<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="575" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of America</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San José, Costa Rica</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-07"><hi rend="italic">September 7, 1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 310.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise that the decree
                            of the Government of Costa Rica, in relation to reciprocity in
                            international copyright, copy and translation of which accompanied my
                            No. 305 of August 30, was published on September 4 in the Official
                            Gazette at this capital, as becoming effective on the 1st of November,
                            1899.</p>
                        <p>With assurances, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William Lawrence Merry</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States Minister.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>